    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes># What's new

- Drive: use Ctrl-A and ESC to select/deselect files [#10839](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10839)
- Drive: implement redesigned DriveTransferStack [#10835](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10835)
- Drive: show file size also on mobile layout [#10830](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10830)
- Drive: support big file upload and improve disk usage for uploading [#10878](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10878)
- Drive: offline login [#10852](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10852)

# Bugfixes

- fixed continue button on plan selector [#10905](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10905)
- Drive: reset progress for each batch of transfers [#10882](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10882)
- fix snackbar position [#10867](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10867)
- extract calendar-related post-login action from PostLoginActions [#10864](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10864)
- Drive/3439 fab only in apps [#10821](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10821)
- Drive: fix operation updates showing again after switching to drive [#10820](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10820)

# Milestone

https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/milestone/439?closed=1</releaseNotes>
